The Senate on Tuesday received a report on the screening of Court of Appeal Justices nominated for the Supreme Court. It was presented by Senator Opeyemi Bamidele. The Ekiti lawmaker chairs the Committee on Judiciary, Human Rights and Legal Matters. After his presentation and call on the Senate to receive the report, Senator Rochas Okorocha seconded. The nominees are Justice M. Lawal Garba – North West, Justice Helen M. Ogunwumiju – South West, Justice Addu Aboki – North West, Justice I. M. M. Saulawa – North West. Others are Justice Adamu Jauro – North East, Justice Samuel C. Oseji – South-South, Justice Tijjani Abubakar – North East, and Justice Emmanuel A. Agim – South-South.